                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.34/188a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-12-09T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1924—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. The <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> this morning carries despatch from
                    Buenos Aires, dated December 8, stating that the Naval Committee of the
                    Brazilian Chamber of Deputies adopted a resolution recommending the construction
                    of 12 warships. The resolution provides for 2 cruisers of approximately 10,000
                    tons each, 4 destroyers of 1,440 tons each, 1 destroyer of 1$800 tons and 5
                    submarines of between 1,300 and 1,500 tons each. The report adds that further
                    aviation development is also recommended. Please cable facts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
